    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I am thinking about whether it's worthwhile to introduce this complexity. \r\nWe have another trick: in order to protect mini reorg during the syncing, if the height of the last header we receive - current head height > 48, then we will discard some head headers.\r\n\r\nSo it means for full sync if the blockchain is not that close to head(e.g. chain is still importing 8K blocks), then headers fetching will continue(for most of the normal case).\r\n",
